        <body>
            <div type="div1" rend="DH-Heading1">
                <head>Introducción</head>
                <p>Encabalgamiento es el desajuste entre la pausa métrica y la sintáctica 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a13a78t84e0","properties":{"formattedCitation":"{\\rtf (Dom\\uc0\\u237{}nguez Caparr\\uc0\\u243{}s, 2000)}","plainCitation":"(Domínguez Caparrós, 2000)"},"citationItems":[{"id":372,"uris":["http://zotero.org/users/3707759/items/GQ7BA63M"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/users/3707759/items/GQ7BA63M"],"itemData":{"id":372,"type":"book","title":"Métrica española","publisher":"Síntesis","publisher-place":"Madrid","event-place":"Madrid","author":[{"family":"Domínguez Caparrós","given":"José"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2000"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Domínguez Caparrós, 2000: 103) que ocurre cuando una unidad de sentido se rompe entre dos versos. Este fenómeno, desde siempre utilizado con distintos fines expresivos (énfasis, ambigüedad, etc.) es difícil de delimitar formalmente. 
                </p>
                <p>El estudio más sistemático realizado para su caracterización en español sigue siendo el realizado en su tesis por Quilis 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a1hr4shuc56","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Quilis, 1964)","plainCitation":"(Quilis, 1964)"},"citationItems":[{"id":527,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/MZU73NXT"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/MZU73NXT"],"itemData":{"id":527,"type":"book","title":"Estructura del encabalgamiento en la métrica española","publisher":"Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Científicas, patronato\" Menéndez y Pelayo,\" Instituto\" Miguel de Cervantes,\"","source":"Google Scholar","note":"00002","author":[{"family":"Quilis","given":"Antonio"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["1964"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(1964). El estudioso experimentó con lecturas de prosa, buscando demostrar qué unidades sintácticas no permiten pausa de sentido en su interior. Basándose en los resultados definió una serie de categorías gramaticales y sintácticas cuya separación en versos distintos produce encabalgamiento. La tipología allí establecida se considera ya clásica. El estudio de Quilis proporciona una definición formal y empírica del fenómeno. Con base en sus reglas se ha creado una herramienta capaz de detectar el encabalgamiento y sus tipos. 
                </p>
                <p>Este póster presenta la interfaz ANJA para el análisis automático del encabalgamiento desde una sencilla aplicación web: 
                    <ref target="http://prf1.org/anja/index/">http://prf1.org/anja/index/</ref>, desarrollada dentro del proyecto ERC POSTDATA GA- 679528
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn1" n="1">
                        <p rend="footnote text"> Este trabajo se enmarca dentro del proyecto de investigación Starting Grant Poetry Standardization and Linked Open Data: POSTDATA (ERC-2015-STG-679528), financiado por el European Research Council (ERC) bajo el programa: European Union´s Horizon 2020 research and innovation programme, dirigido como Investigador Principal por la profesora Elena González-Blanco, LINHD UNED (
                            <ref target="http://postdata.linhd.es/">http://postdata.linhd.es/</ref>).
                        </p>
                    </note>.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="div1" rend="DH-Heading1">
                <head>Estado del arte</head>
                <p>La naturaleza formal del análisis métrico lo hace un campo propicio para su tratamiento computacional 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a1711n8sdfn","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Birnbaum and Thorsen, 2015)","plainCitation":"(Birnbaum and Thorsen, 2015)"},"citationItems":[{"id":540,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/SZX4IMRJ"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/SZX4IMRJ"],"itemData":{"id":540,"type":"paper-conference","title":"Markup and meter: Using XML tools to teach a computer to think about versification","container-title":"Balisage: The Markup Conference","source":"Google Scholar","URL":"http://www.balisage.net/Proceedings/vol15/print/Birnbaum01/BalisageVol15-Birnbaum01.html","note":"00002","shortTitle":"Markup and meter","author":[{"family":"Birnbaum","given":"David J."},{"family":"Thorsen","given":"Elise"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2015"]]},"accessed":{"date-parts":[["2017",4,22]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Birnbaum and Thorsen, 2015;
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a62fi7049n","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Delente and Renault, 2015)","plainCitation":"(Delente and Renault, 2015)"},"citationItems":[{"id":489,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/VZWBTWI2"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/VZWBTWI2"],"itemData":{"id":489,"type":"article-journal","title":"Outils et métrique: un tour d'horizon","container-title":"Langages","page":"5–22","issue":"3","source":"Google Scholar","note":"00001","shortTitle":"Outils et métrique","author":[{"family":"Delente","given":"Éliane"},{"family":"Renault","given":"Richard"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2015"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?> Delente and Renault, 2015). El procesamiento del lenguaje natural (PLN) ofrece muchas posibilidades para la métrica, pues las reglas de definición lingüística permiten llevar a cabo análisis y extracción automática de grandes cantidades de información de corpus textuales. 
                </p>
                <p>Para la automatización del análisis métrico en español destacamos los estudios de escansión silábica y acentual de Navarro-Colorado 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a152ofsqonf","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Navarro-Colorado, 2017)","plainCitation":"(Navarro-Colorado, 2017)"},"citationItems":[{"id":498,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/CQK7XFVG"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/CQK7XFVG"],"itemData":{"id":498,"type":"article-journal","title":"A metrical scansion system for fixed-metre Spanish poetry","container-title":"Digital Scholarship in the Humanities","source":"academic.oup.com","URL":"https://academic.oup.com/dsh/article-abstract/doi/10.1093/llc/fqx009/3064339/A-metrical-scansion-system-for-fixed-metre-Spanish","DOI":"10.1093/llc/fqx009","note":"00002","journalAbbreviation":"Digital Scholarship Humanities","author":[{"family":"Navarro-Colorado","given":"Borja"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2017"]]},"accessed":{"date-parts":[["2017",4,19]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(2017), Agirrezabal 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"aut9qaud1g","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Agirrezabal, 2017)","plainCitation":"(Agirrezabal, 2017)"},"citationItems":[{"id":1122,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/NDI4SBZW"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/NDI4SBZW"],"itemData":{"id":1122,"type":"thesis","title":"Automatic Scansion of Poetry","publisher":"Universidad del País Vasco","publisher-place":"San Sebastián/Donosti","event-place":"San Sebastián/Donosti","author":[{"family":"Agirrezabal","given":"Manex"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2017"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(2017) y Gervás 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a1u243kq4dl","properties":{"formattedCitation":"{\\rtf (Gerv\\uc0\\u225{}s, 2000)}","plainCitation":"(Gervás, 2000)","dontUpdate":true},"citationItems":[{"id":1127,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/ZFBT9N5S"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/ZFBT9N5S"],"itemData":{"id":1127,"type":"chapter","title":"A Logic Programming Application for the Analysis of Spanish Verse","container-title":"Computational Logic—CL 2000","publisher":"Springer Berlin Heidelberg","publisher-place":"Berlin","page":"1330-1344","event-place":"Berlin","author":[{"family":"Gervás","given":"Pablo"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2000"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(2000). También los trabajos de generación automática de poesía con patrones métricos 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"aar7h14imv","properties":{"formattedCitation":"{\\rtf (Gerv\\uc0\\u225{}s, 2000b)}","plainCitation":"(Gervás, 2000b)"},"citationItems":[{"id":561,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/HNDJRDIR"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/HNDJRDIR"],"itemData":{"id":561,"type":"paper-conference","title":"Wasp: Evaluation of different strategies for the automatic generation of spanish verse","container-title":"Proceedings of the AISB-00 symposium on creative & cultural aspects of AI","page":"93–100","source":"Google Scholar","URL":"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Pablo_Gervas/publication/228609235_Wasp_Evaluation_of_different_strategies_for_the_automatic_generation_of_spanish_verse/links/00b4952aada6407047000000.pdf","note":"00071","shortTitle":"Wasp","author":[{"family":"Gervás","given":"Pablo"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2000"]]},"accessed":{"date-parts":[["2017",4,22]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Gervás, 2000b) y 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"IqQ3WEcx","properties":{"formattedCitation":"{\\rtf (Gerv\\uc0\\u225{}s, 2015)}","plainCitation":"(Gervás, 2015)"},"citationItems":[{"id":563,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/7TDNKEXM"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/7TDNKEXM"],"itemData":{"id":563,"type":"paper-conference","title":"Tightening the Constraints on Form and Content for an Existing Computer Poet","container-title":"AISB Convention 2015","source":"Google Scholar","URL":"http://eprints.sim.ucm.es/37000/","note":"00001","author":[{"family":"Gervás","given":"Pablo"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2015"]]},"accessed":{"date-parts":[["2017",4,22]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Gervás, 2015). 
                </p>
                <p>En el campo de las interfaces cabe distinguir entre aquellas que exploran datos de textos ya analizados, recogidos en una base de datos, y aquellas que permiten la entrada y análisis de cualquier poema. Del primer tipo destacamos For Better For Verse
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn2" n="2">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="http://prosody.lib.virginia.edu/">http://prosody.lib.virginia.edu/</ref>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a2nfmtb449o","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Tucker, 2011)","plainCitation":"(Tucker, 2011)"},"citationItems":[{"id":1152,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/ZIS5PXPE"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/ZIS5PXPE"],"itemData":{"id":1152,"type":"article-journal","title":"Poetic data and the news from poems: A for better for verse memoir","container-title":"Victorian Poetry","page":"267–281","volume":"49","issue":"2","source":"Google Scholar","shortTitle":"Poetic data and the news from poems","author":[{"family":"Tucker","given":"Herbert F."}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2011"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Tucker, 2011) y Database of Czech Metre
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn3" n="3">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="http://versologie.cz/v2/web_content/">http://versologie.cz/v2/web_content/</ref>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a2ei4qt3l8","properties":{"formattedCitation":"{\\rtf (Plech\\uc0\\u225{}\\uc0\\u269{} and Kol\\uc0\\u225{}r, 2015)}","plainCitation":"(Plecháč and Kolár, 2015)"},"citationItems":[{"id":1157,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/TINCAKV7"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/TINCAKV7"],"itemData":{"id":1157,"type":"article-journal","title":"The Corpus of Czech Verse","container-title":"Studia Metrica et Poetica","page":"107–118","volume":"2","issue":"1","source":"Google Scholar","author":[{"family":"Plecháč","given":"Petr"},{"family":"Kolár","given":"Robert"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2015"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Plecháč and Kolár, 2015). Entre las que permiten introducir textos destacamos, en español, la ligada a la herramienta de Navarro-Colorado
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn4" n="4">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="http://adso.gplsi.es/index.php/es/demostracion/">http://adso.gplsi.es/index.php/es/demostracion/</ref>
                        </p>
                    </note>, que analiza versos endecasílabos. Otros sitios con interfaz de entrada para análisis métrico son Separarensílabas
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn5" n="5">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="http://www.separarensilabas.com/index.php">http://www.separarensilabas.com/index.php</ref>
                        </p>
                    </note> o Lexiquetos
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn6" n="6">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="http://lexiquetos.org/silio/">http://lexiquetos.org/silio/</ref>
                        </p>
                    </note>. En otras lenguas destacamos Metricalizer
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn7" n="7">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="https://metricalizer.de/en/metrikanalyse/poem">https://metricalizer.de/en/metrikanalyse/poem</ref>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a147qktvdo","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Bobenhausen and Hammerich, 2015)","plainCitation":"(Bobenhausen and Hammerich, 2015)"},"citationItems":[{"id":423,"uris":["http://zotero.org/users/3707759/items/JR4P2QG8"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/users/3707759/items/JR4P2QG8"],"itemData":{"id":423,"type":"article-journal","title":"Métrique littéraire, métrique linguistique et métrique algorithmique de l'allemand mises en jeu dans le programme Metricalizer2","container-title":"Langages","page":"67–88","issue":"3","source":"Google Scholar","author":[{"family":"Bobenhausen","given":"Klemens"},{"family":"Hammerich","given":"Benjamin"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2015"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Bobenhausen and Hammerich, 2015) para alemán, Aoidos
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn8" n="8">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="http://aoidos.ufsc.br/">http://aoidos.ufsc.br/</ref>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a2h1bsuf6hj","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Mittmann, 2016)","plainCitation":"(Mittmann, 2016)"},"citationItems":[{"id":827,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/604703/items/X7859Z3V"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/604703/items/X7859Z3V"],"itemData":{"id":827,"type":"article-journal","title":"Escansão automática de versos em português","source":"Google Scholar","URL":"https://repositorio.ufsc.br/handle/123456789/175819","note":"00000","author":[{"family":"Mittmann","given":"Adiel"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2016"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Mittmann, 2016) para portugués y español, y RhymeDesign
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn9" n="9">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="http://www.sci.utah.edu/~nmccurdy/rhymeDesign/">http://www.sci.utah.edu/~nmccurdy/rhymeDesign/</ref>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a2lga04s1b6","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(McCurdy et al., 2015)","plainCitation":"(McCurdy et al., 2015)"},"citationItems":[{"id":1142,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/T5IE63ZA"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/T5IE63ZA"],"itemData":{"id":1142,"type":"chapter","title":"Rhymedesign: A tool for analyzing sonic devices in poetry","container-title":"Proceedings of the Fourth Workshop on Computational Linguistics for Literature","page":"12–22","source":"Google Scholar","shortTitle":"Rhymedesign","author":[{"family":"McCurdy","given":"Nina"},{"family":"Srikumar","given":"Vivek"},{"family":"Meyer","given":"Miriah"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2015"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(McCurdy et al., 2015) especializado en rima en inglés.
                </p>
                <p>Una interfaz para el análisis del encabalgamiento representa, sin embargo, una novedad en el campo.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="div1" rend="DH-Heading1">
                <head> Herramienta y resultados </head>
                <p>El programa de detección del encabalgamiento en español, basado en PLN, se desarrolló en 2016-2017 y fue evaluado sobre dos corpus de test de distintos periodos 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a8vtl0rkqc","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Ruiz et al., 2017)","plainCitation":"(Ruiz et al., 2017)"},"citationItems":[{"id":1002,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/J5BAIM6A"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/J5BAIM6A"],"itemData":{"id":1002,"type":"paper-conference","title":"Enjambment Detection in a Large Diachronic Corpus of Spanish Sonnets","container-title":"Proceedings of the Joint SIGHUM Workshop on Computational Linguistics for Cultural Heritage, Social Sciences, Humanities and Literature","publisher":"Association for Computational Linguistics","page":"27–32","source":"Google Scholar","author":[{"family":"Ruiz","given":"Pablo"},{"family":"Martínez Cantón","given":"Clara"},{"family":"Poibeau","given":"Thierry"},{"family":"González-Blanco","given":"Elena"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2017"]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Ruiz et al., 2017). ANJA proporciona una interfaz web simple para este programa. El sistema consta de tres componentes: módulo de preprocesado para uniformar el formato de los poemas, pipeline de PLN (basada en IXA Pipes 
                    <?biblio ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION {"citationID":"a156unuhkub","properties":{"formattedCitation":"(Agerri et al., 2014)","plainCitation":"(Agerri et al., 2014)"},"citationItems":[{"id":500,"uris":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/2JB37MX6"],"uri":["http://zotero.org/groups/1263792/items/2JB37MX6"],"itemData":{"id":500,"type":"paper-conference","title":"IXA pipeline: Efficient and Ready to Use Multilingual NLP tools.","container-title":"Proceedings of LREC 2014, the 9th International Language Resources and Evaluation Conference","publisher-place":"Reykjavik,Iceland","page":"3823–3828","volume":"2014","source":"Google Scholar","event-place":"Reykjavik,Iceland","URL":"http://www.lrec-conf.org/proceedings/lrec2014/pdf/775_Paper.pdf","note":"00068","shortTitle":"IXA pipeline","author":[{"family":"Agerri","given":"Rodrigo"},{"family":"Bermudez","given":"Josu"},{"family":"Rigau","given":"German"}],"issued":{"date-parts":[["2014"]]},"accessed":{"date-parts":[["2017",4,20]]}}}],"schema":"https://github.com/citation-style-language/schema/raw/master/csl-citation.json"}?>(Agerri et al., 2014) para POS-tagging, constituyentes y dependencias sintácticas) y módulo de detección de encabalgamiento (basado en reglas y diccionarios) y ampliamente documentado en el sitio web
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn10" n="10">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="https://sites.google.com/site/spanishenjambment/">
                                <hi rend="underline color(1155CC)">https://sites.google.com/site/spanishenjambment/</hi>
                            </ref>
                        </p>
                    </note>. Se ha utilizado esta herramienta para etiquetar un corpus de más de 4000 sonetos alojado y documentado en
                    <ref target="https://github.com/pruizf/disco/">
                        <hi rend="underline color(1155CC)">https://github.com/postdataproject/disco</hi>
                    </ref>.
                </p>
                <p>El código de la herramienta de detección de encabalgamientos está disponible en 
                    <ref target="https://bitbucket.org/pruizf/anja_public/">https://bitbucket.org/pruizf/anja_public/</ref>.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="div1" rend="DH-Heading1">
                <head>Interfaz gráfica de usuario</head>
                <p>ANJA es una interfaz pública y gratuita, alojada en: 
                    <ref target="http://prf1.org/anja/index/">http://prf1.org/anja/index/</ref>. Permite cargar los poemas que el usuario decida y analizarlos en el momento. También ofrece la carga de archivos ZIP que contengan archivos en texto plano.
                </p>
                <p>La interfaz de usuario está construida con el framework Django (Python), con las plantillas de Bootstrap 3. Las vistas de Django se llaman con AJAX para poblar los elementos de la UI. Para el análisis de PLN, Django accede a servicios web Java (IXA Pipes) implementados en nuestro servidor.</p>
                <p>ANJA presenta dos ventanas de navegación (Fig. 1), la principal, para introducir poemas, a la derecha y, a la izquierda, una mínima guía de uso que explica su funcionamiento y enlaza a la web del proyecto.</p>
                <figure>
                    <graphic n="1001" width="15.828344444444445cm" height="5.267158333333334cm" url="Pictures/2c2b77178ab6b500074f08d76ffe598a.png" rend="inline"/>
                    <head>Captura de ANJA</head>
                </figure>
                <p>Los resultados se ofrecen dos formatos: 
                    <hi rend="italic">Standoff</hi> (tipo de encabalgamiento y línea), e 
                    <hi rend="italic">Inline</hi> (etiquetado gramatical y tipo de encabalgamiento por línea, ver Fig. 2 para 
                    <hi rend="italic">Inline</hi>). Las anotaciones PLN en que se basa en sistema se ofrecen en las pestañas 
                    <hi rend="italic">PosTags</hi> (etiquetas gramaticales) y 
                    <hi rend="italic">FullNLP</hi> (pipeline completa). 
                </p>
                <p>El enlace 
                    <hi rend="bold">legend</hi>
                    <note place="foot" xml:id="ftn11" n="11">
                        <p rend="footnote text">
                            <ref target="https://sites.google.com/site/spanishenjambment/legend">https://sites.google.com/site/spanishenjambment/legend</ref>
                        </p>
                    </note> da acceso a la leyenda que explica los tipos de encabalgamiento, las etiquetas gramaticales y otras convenciones de representación: 
                </p>
                <figure>
                    <graphic n="1002" width="16.102980555555554cm" height="5.828630555555556cm" url="Pictures/81ac689c2b9c94488c8a4943dba75b83.png" rend="inline"/>
                    <head>Anotaciones de encabalgamiento en formato 
                        <hi rend="italic">Inline</hi>
                    </head>
                </figure>
                <p>La existencia de una aplicación web simple para la utilización esta herramienta la hace accesible para una gama mucho más amplia de usuarios.</p>
